cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on language emergence and communication in multi-agent systems. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses graph convolutional networks to support the evolution of language and cooperation. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes strong baseline models for the referential game and discusses the agents' ability to generalize beyond training samples. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper explores communication and cooperation in multi-agent systems. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses an image-based referential game as motivation for the graph referential game.
